This paper focuses on the development and testing of autonomous vehicles, which involves software engineering (cs.SE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of signal temporal logic (STL) as a requirements language and the support for machine learning components in the system design suggest a strong emphasis on software engineering and artificial intelligence. The inclusion of models of sensors and the vehicle environment suggests a focus on robotics and systems and control. Overall, this paper spans multiple sub-categories of computer science, but the emphasis on software engineering and artificial intelligence make cs.SE and cs.AI the most likely categories.
